  m_Name: Mushroom_17_Oyster
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Hollowfen.Data.MushroomFieldGuideData
  _id: oyster
  _commonName: Oyster Mushroom
  _latinName: Pleurotus ostreatus
  _edibility: 0
  _edibilityLabel: "Edible \u2014 choice"
  _description: "A reliable woodland edible \u2014 soft, fan-shaped caps that grow
    in shelving clusters straight from dead and dying hardwood. Mild, sweet flavor;
    almost no dangerous lookalikes once you learn the shape and smell."
  _idFeatures:
  - Fan- or oyster-shaped cap, off-white to grey to pale tan
  - Decurrent gills running down a stubby off-center stem (or no stem at all)
  - "Grows in tight, overlapping shelves on hardwood \u2014 beech, oak, willow"
  - White spore print
  - Faint anise-and-almond smell when fresh
  _habitat: "Dead or dying hardwood \u2014 fallen logs, standing trunks, stumps.
    Never on the ground."
  _season: Late autumn through early spring after the first frost
  _lookalikes: "Angel's Wings (Pleurocybella porrigens) \u2014 pure-white, much thinner
    flesh, grows on conifers; was long thought safe but has caused fatalities and
    should be avoided. The Bitter Oyster (Panellus stipticus) is bioluminescent and
    bitter; small and tough."
  _notes: "Look UP \u2014 oysters fruit at chest height and above on standing trunks.
    Cut the cluster cleanly with a knife; tearing damages the mycelium and reduces
    next year's flush."
